state.unicode: When his mood reaches 100%, Achilles will have a mood swing which will affect both his army and his faction. At that point, his advisors will offer gifts to soothe his strong emotions.

Achilles is prone to grandiose mood swings that can severely impact those under his command. These bars represent the three powerful emotions that can sway him: rage, indignation and grief.
Achilles is grieving the deaths of his allies. The population mourns along with their leader and have turned to the gods for guidance.
Achilles is currently enraged following recent setbacks and is consumed by thoughts of war. The population and economy will only suffer as a result!
Achilles is currently indignant and is indulging in endless feasts. Diplomacy suffers, but the farmers, bolstered by the festivities, redouble their efforts in the fields.
